top ten forever ! this is a must have for each and everyone who loves comedies with a deeper sense of humor . the story is as small as it should be to be written on the back of a stamp : three guys go to prison and have to share the same cell , they do n't like each other , but they have to escape together . the film works without many words . the characters are so obvious that they do n't need much of a dialogue to be funny . this is a trio never seen before : roberto benigni at his best , john lurie as the silent man , and tom waits mythologizing himself as always . ... and not to forget the thrilling music of tom waits , which turns the opening of the film to mere art . definitively the best jarmush film and a cult of the eighties . have fun ! ||| top ten forever ! this is a must have for each and everyone who loves comedies with a deeper sense of humor . the story is as small as it should be to be written on the back of a stamp : three guys go to jail and have to share the same cell , they do not like each other , but they have to escape together . the film works without many words . the characters are so obvious that they do not need much of a dialogue to be funny . this is a trio never seen before : roberto benigni at his best , john lurie as the silent man , and tom waits mythologizing himself as always . ... and not to forget the thrilling music of tom waits , which turns the opening of the film to mere art . definitively the best jarmush and a cult film of the eighties . have fun !